---
/**
 * /spike/appshell/ — first half of the AppShell persistence spike.
 *
 * NOT a production route. Lives under /spike/ specifically so it can be
 * included in builds without polluting hub navigation.
 *
 * Pair with /spike/appshell/dome/ — clicking back-and-forth is the spike.
 */
import AppShell from '../../../components/AppShell.astro';
---

<AppShell title="P31 spike — AppShell home" routeName="home">
  <h1>Track 2.5 spike — AppShell home</h1>
  <p>
    The starfield behind this page lives in a single canvas at the body level.
    Click <em>dome</em> below; the camera should lerp inward over ~600&nbsp;ms.
    No black flash. No re-init. The same canvas DOM node and WebGL context
    persist across the navigation.
  </p>
  <nav class="p31-spike-nav" aria-label="Spike routes">
    <a href="/spike/appshell/" aria-current="page">home</a>
    <a href="/spike/appshell/dome/">dome</a>
  </nav>
  <p>
    If the camera teleports instead of lerping, or the points flash black,
    or <code>canvas identity</code> in the stats below changes between navs,
    the spike is failing. See <code>docs/SPIKE-APPSHELL-PERSISTENCE.md</code>
    in the home repo for stop conditions.
  </p>
</AppShell>
